@DATABASE FreeCop Documentation
@NODE MaIN "FreeCop Documentation"

                     Colorboy/Mystic presents ya now

                                'FREECOP'

                       Click On Wanted Information!

                              @{" Description  " LINK DSC}
                              @{" Introduction " LINK INT}
                              @{" Usage        " LINK USG}
                              @{" Installation " LINK INS}
                              @{" Last Words   " LINK LWD}
@ENDNODE
@NODE DSC "Short Description"

                          This Program Fixes:

                          - The Copperlist

                          - Bitplanes

                          - Intena And DMA-Bits

                              @{" Introduction " LINK INT}
                              @{" Usage        " LINK USG}
                              @{" Installation " LINK INS}
                              @{" Last Words   " LINK LWD}

                              @{" Main Menu    " LINK MaIN}
@ENDNODE

@NODE INT "Introduction"

 Imagine  The  Following  Situation:
 ===================================

 You Run An Intro And After Exiting You Only See Some Planes Scrumbling And
 Nothing  Is Able To Be Read Anymore, But You Don't Want To Reset! You Want
 To Watch More Intros On Your Disk Or Harddrive.

 This  Tool  Will  Try To Refresh The Copperlist To The Old State As It Was
 Before Executing The Intro. In Some Cases You May Recognize That The Mouse
 Does Not Work Anymore. If Possible This Is Going To Be Restored, Too.

                              @{" Usage        " LINK USG}
                              @{" Installation " LINK INS}
                              @{" Last Words   " LINK LWD}

                              @{" Main Menu    " LINK MaIN}
@ENDNODE
@NODE USG "Usage"

                  You Have Nothing To Do More As To Type

                                'FREECOP'

                          In Your CLI Or Shell.

 The  Programm  Will Be Loaded And Executed. If The Screen And Mousepointer
 Are Normal Again Then You Did Run It With Success.

                              @{" Installation " LINK INS}
                              @{" Last Words   " LINK LWD}

                              @{" Main Menu    " LINK MaIN}
@ENDNODE
@NODE INS "Installation"

                   For  Easy  Use  Just  Copy The File

                                'FREECOP'

   Into Your C-Directory Of The Harddrive Or Simply On The Intro Disk.

                              @{" Last Words   " LINK LWD}

                              @{" Main Menu    " LINK MaIN}
@ENDNODE
@NODE LWD "Last Words"

 I  Hope  You  Don't  Think It's Lame To Release Such A Simple Tool. If Yes
 Then I Ask You, Why It Is Neccessary To Code Something Like This?!
 
 I'll  Give  You The Answer! A Lot Of Demo And Intro Coders Are !Unable! To
 Refresh  The Copperlist In Their Products. To Prove That, Just Have A Look
 At  The  File  'yvonne2.exe'  From Melon Dezign And Many Intros From Other
 Cool Elite Crews!

 Note,  That I Don't Want To Say With This, That Lemon Dezign Is Lame! Cool
